titleStmt.title: This following address (which ws signed by 86 gentlemen and others) was delivered by Collonel Stroud, Governour of Dover Castle, to his Majesty, before he went to Windsom. To the king's most excellent Majesty. The humble address of the truly loyal subjects of the town and port of Dover.
